Today I woke up and chose coding. Started my day off by creating a new sails application. `Sails js` is an `MVC` Framework based on Nodejs.
I wanted to improve mostly on my server-side skills, and lately the tools I have been using to maintain my daily routine have been turning their back, and asking for a plan upgrade!

Hard Luck!!

Main thing I wanted to do was to sync my Todos with `Google Calendar`. As an android user, I prefer the Google Calendar which is obviously free to help me with my schedules.
Anyway, so I searched and found the open APIs that google provide for creating Calendar events, and there it is. That is my playground.
The options for using JS frameworks are myriad. Each one of them was created to solve something unique or to give a unique experience. What problem does Sails js solve?
Sails was created back in 2012 by `Mike McNeil` to assist his team in building scalable Node.js projects for startup and enterprise customers.[source:[https://sailsjs.com/about](https://sailsjs.com/about)]
`Sails js` provides similar MVC structure as Ruby on Rails but has additional support for the requirements of modern apps: data-driven APIs with a scalable, service-oriented architecture. Having an MVC layer above Nodejs really structures the code and makes it convenient to develop on.
I am trying to explore more on Sails and how I can make my application better using its feature to the fullest. Currently I am implementing two things which includes google authentication and creating tasks and sync that with calendar events.
Soon will be making the repo and work public.